<TITLE> Miandad quits as director general of PCB </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KARACHI, Jan 28 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Former captain and coach Javed Miandad resigned as director general of the Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) on Wednesday, saying he was unhappy with the role. "I don't think my experience and knowledge should be restricted to looking after only domestic cricket," Miandad told Reuters. "I am not satisfied with the responsibilities and area of work given to me in my contract." Miandad, who was appointed in November, said he initially thought he would be looking after all cricket matters, including national team issues and selection. "The chairman had issued a circular last month outlining my responsibilities and authority but the contract is different," Miandad said. "I have no grievance with anyone, and I have told the chairman this, but I can't accept my reduced role." Miandad, who played in 124 tests, quit the day after Younis Khan replaced Shoaib Malik as skipper and said he had opposed the change of leadership. "My resignation is not because of that issue," he said. "I have resigned on a matter of principle.
